column4: Anyone know why transferring of files from MSN to Gaim is so slow? its driving me around the bend
2.30kb/s is way to slow back on windows it used to be at least 50kb/s and I've downloaded files that fast before on Linux but not through MSN to Gaim...any ideas?
gaim is not that good
with file transfers that is
you run dapper or edgy?
er...6.06 lol I'm not too sure which one that is heh, what should I use instead?
well 6.06 has gaim 1.* and 6.10 has gaim 2.* which has better support for file transfers
to upgrade try running 'sudo update-manager -c'
oh ok, well I can't get 6.10 so heh :( can I get 2.* on 6.06?
it takes a while
well it looks like I've started upgrading to 6.10 heh, will I lose all my stuff? not that I have alot on here...but
probably not, but there is a teensy weensy possibility
ok well I'm not too bothered, mainly bookmarks and favorites all of which found via google, er..a few files nothing that essential
don't know if you come from a land called windows. But upgrading actually works as you would want
all programs get upgraded too
yeah I've just seen the file size then, too big for now anyway, maybe on a Saturday but not now :( maybe just the upgrades not the new ubuntu version
last time I upgraded the desktop wouldn't load, what would I do if this happen again?
? I can't upgrade until I know waht I'm doing otherwise I'll mess it all up again
hehe that might be a good idea
though i don't think there is a big chance you will mess things up
last time I upgraded, I don't know if it was that or something else but when I loged on the screen was just the background nothing else started up
mmm okay... too bad
